            "description": "Role: Managing BPM Consultant & advisory services, driving results for key deliverables such as 1st GoLive in Dec 2013, with involvement on all activities needed to run this program\n\nRabobank Group is an international financial services provider with cooperative basis, active in banking, capital management, leasing, insurance and real estate. \nWithin the Netherlands the focus for Rabobank is on financial services, the international focus is on food- and agriculture business. Rabobank Group consists of independent local banks and their central organisation Rabobank Nederland with some specialised subsidiaries.\n\nRabobank Group has more than 10 million customers globally, and more than 60,000 employees. Within the Netherlands, Rabobank services 7.5 million customers, with 6,000 employees. Rabobank International (wholesale and int. retail bank), has 15,000 employees across 27 countries, and 29,000 employees servicing customers through its local banks.\n\nThe program Corporate Lending has the related ambition to coordinate all ICT aspects regarding the delivery and maintenance of credit products for all corporate advice / corporate relations customers, regardless of distribution channel (local banks as well as FGH and/or CC and/or DLL).\n\nImplement a case management and/or process management solution for loan origination, maintenance (credit management) and services. This solution will be made available for the 139 independent local Rabobanks as well as their customers. The main challenge is to deliver a user friendly cross-channel platform. This platform needs to enable operational excellence (standardization and efficiency) for the retail market and at the same time support customization of the finance processes at runtime on a case to case basis.",
